    Provide diagnostic summary of an NMTRAN dataset

    nm_summary.Rd

    This function is intended to provide a high level overview of variables derived during a data assembly. The output of this function will provide the user with a pdf file containing a series of tables to help the user better understand distributions within the derived data set.

    nm_summary(.data, .spec, ..., .type = "tables")

    Arguments

    .data

    a data frame

    .spec

    a yspec object

    ...

    arguments passed through from methods (currently none)

    .type

    specify desired output of "tables" or "figures". Default is "tables"

    Examples

    
nm_spec <- yspec::ys_load(system.file("derived", "pk.yml", package = "mrgda"))

nm <- readr::read_csv(system.file("derived", "pk.csv", package = "mrgda"), na = ".")
#> Rows: 2534 Columns: 28
